  "prompt": "In which cases does Instagram send a notification to your Facebook friends stating you have joined Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Instagram does **not** send notifications to your Facebook friends stating that you have joined Instagram. However, there are a few scenarios where your Facebook friends might discover that you\u2019ve joined Instagram:\n\n1. **Linking Facebook and Instagram Accounts**: If you link your Instagram account to your Facebook account, Instagram may suggest your profile to your Facebook friends through features like \"People You May Know\" on Instagram or \"Suggested Friends\" on Facebook. This is not a direct notification but a recommendation based on your linked accounts.\n\n2. **Facebook Friend Syncing**: If you allow Instagram to sync your Facebook friends when setting up your account, Instagram may suggest your profile to your Facebook friends or vice versa. Again, this is not a notification but a suggestion.\n\n3. **Posting Instagram Content on Facebook**: If you share your Instagram posts or stories to your Facebook profile or page, your Facebook friends might see this activity and realize you\u2019ve joined Instagram.\n\n4. **Searching Manually**: Your Facebook friends might manually search for your Instagram username or find you through mutual connections.\n\nTo avoid your Facebook friends discovering your Instagram account, you can:\n- Unlink your Facebook and Instagram accounts.\n- Avoid syncing your Facebook friends on Instagram.\n- Set your Instagram account to private to control who can see your profile and content.\n\nAlways review your privacy settings on both platforms to manage how your information is shared.",
